AUMAXrjguvAmMPjycSJS0v7jKMOeTCw ) , and AWS is still the most important hos=
ting platform that will host plenty of other models for all of those applic=
ations and datasets already in place. Moreover, while Llama is in many resp=
ects now an obvious choice for startups building products that incorporate =
AI, that choice may entail foreclosing a future acquisition from one of the=
 giants, because they would then run afoul of Meta=E2=80=99s license.

I could certainly see this situation evolving over time: if Llama doesn=E2=
=80=99t get as much traction as Meta hopes then it may open it up to big co=
mpanies too; if it gets massive traction then Apple and Amazon in particula=
r may have no choice but to make a deal to make the most dominant model ava=
ilable on their platforms. =E2=80=9CMost dominant model available=E2=80=9D =
is a big =E2=80=9Cif=E2=80=9D, of course, but open source is a pretty darn =
big accelerant, both for Llama specifically and AI generally.

